---
import ProseLayout from '../layouts/ProseLayout.astro';
---

<ProseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How GLANCE Apps handles your data. Short version: we don't collect it."
  lastUpdated="May 2025"
>
  <p class="lead">
    Short version: GLANCE Apps does not collect, store, or share your personal
    data. Your information stays on your device.
  </p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    GLANCE Apps is an independent software developer publishing iOS applications
    including dayGLANCE, lifeGLANCE, and others. This privacy policy covers all
    apps published under the GLANCE Apps name (collectively, "the Apps") and the
    glance-apps.com website.
  </p>

  <h2>Data we do not collect</h2>
  <p>
    Our Apps are designed to operate entirely on your device. We do not:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Require you to create an account</li>
    <li>Collect personally identifiable information</li>
    <li>Transmit your journal entries, notes, goals, or any app content to our servers</li>
    <li>Track your location</li>
    <li>Use advertising identifiers</li>
    <li>Sell or share your data with third parties</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
  <p>
    All content you create within our Apps (entries, notes, goals, preferences,
    and similar data) is stored locally on your device using Apple's standard
    on-device storage mechanisms. This data remains under your control at all
    times.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use iCloud Backup, Apple may back up this data as part of your
    standard device backup. This is governed by{' '}
    <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Apple's Privacy Policy
    </a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Calendar access</h2>
  <p>
    Some apps (such as dayGLANCE) may request access to your device's calendar
    to display your schedule. This access is read-only, used only to display
    information within the app, and no calendar data is transmitted outside your
    device. You can revoke this permission at any time in iOS Settings.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We do not use third-party analytics services. If you have opted into Apple's
    App Analytics program through your device settings, Apple may share
    aggregated, anonymized crash and usage data with us via App Store Connect.
    This data cannot be used to identify you individually.
  </p>

  <h2>This website</h2>
  <p>
    The glance-apps.com website is a static site served via Vercel. Vercel may
    collect standard web server logs (IP address, request times, page URLs) for
    operational purposes. We do not use cookies, tracking pixels, or analytics
    scripts on this site.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Our Apps are not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
    information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the "Last updated"
    date at the top of this page. Continued use of our Apps after such changes
    constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about our privacy practices? We're happy to answer them.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href="mailto:privacy@glance-apps.com">privacy@glance-apps.com</a>
  </p>
</ProseLayout>
